 &#4872;&#4709;&#4648;&#4961; &#4768;&#4637;&#4619;&#4781;&#4961; &#4808;&#4773;&#4633;&#4961; &#4808;&#4616;&#4720;&#4961; &#4720;&#4781;&#4616;&#4961; &#4611;&#4845;&#4635;</span><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 115%;">[fol. 31rb]</span></span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#4758;&#4725;&#4961; &#4808;&#4637;&#4661;&#4616;&#4961; &#4872;&#4709;&#4648;&#4961; &#4874;&#4846;&#4653;&#4874;&#4661;&#4961; &#4672;&#4658;&#4661;&#4961; &#4768;&#4704;&#4961; &#4632;&#4757;&#4936;&#4657;&#4961; &#4840;&#4611;&#4617;&#4961; &#4768;&#4636;&#4757;&#4962;</span></span></span></p><foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                        <note>The colopnoh states that the Ms. was completed on the 30th of Gǝnbot  in the year of mercy 1885, during the time of the Evangelist Matthew (= 6 June 1893 A.D.).&#xD;
Besides, it mentions the name of the donor (s. Additio 1) Ḍäḥayä Lǝda and of his wife Wälättä Giyorgis, his father Gäbrä ʾAmlak, his mother Wälättä Täklä Haymanot  and priest Gäbrä Giyorgis.</note>
                     </colophon>
